news.summary: Crown Castle raised its annual site rental revenue forecast for the second time. The real estate investment trust derives majority of its revenue from leasing out tower infrastructure to U.S. wireless carriers.
news.article_text:
(Reuters) -Wireless tower operator Crown Castle on Wednesday raised its annual site rental revenue forecast for the second time, helped by steady demand for wireless infrastructure services.

Crown Castle derives majority of its revenue from leasing out tower infrastructure to U.S. wireless carriers such as AT&T, T-Mobile US, and Verizon Communications on a long-term basis.

news.headline: Dan Schulman, the former CEO of PayPal, Takes the Helm at Verizon
news.summary: Dan Schulman served as the PayPal (NASDAQ:PYPL) CEO since 2014 and stepped down in 2023. And now is appointed as the CEO of Verizon (NYSE:VZ) on October 6, 2025 to steer the company navigating slowing business growth and major acquisition
news.article_text:
This article first appeared on GuruFocus.

Dan Schulman served as the PayPal (NASDAQ:PYPL) CEO since 2014 and stepped down in 2023. And now is appointed as the CEO of Verizon (NYSE:VZ) on October 6, 2025 to steer the company navigating slowing business growth and major acquisition.
